  <front>
   <head>SONG. TO ALMERIA.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">THOUGH since I lov'd an age is flown,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The blissful hour you still postpone;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ah! lovely Maid, no longer frown,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But each fond hope with rapture crown.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor think, though lur'd by Angel charms,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That Time will linger in thy arms;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Oh! no; his scythe shall crop the rose</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That on thy cheek divinely blows.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But ere the russian riot there,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To Nature yield, enchanting fair;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor more my ardent wish reprove,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For know, Life's richest boon is Love.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
